STEP-3
PATH COMPRESSION---> IF A VERY BIG GRAPH, TO FIND THE PARENT ITS VERY TOUGH CUS HAVE TO TRAVERSE ALL TEH NODES, SO WE CMPRESS THE PATHS
int findUPar(int node)
{
    if(node==parent[node])
        return node;

    return parent[node] = findUPar(parent[node]);
}

STEP-4
UNION--> TO CONNECT VERTICES OF GRAPH
Suppose:

1     4
|     |
2     5

We connect:

union(2,5);

Now they should become one group

STEP-5
UNION BY SIZE----> IF THERES ANY CHNAGE IN THE SUZE IF WE JOINED ANY POINTS OF GRAPH SOO,
void unionBySize(int u,int v)
{
    int ulp_u = findUPar(u);
    int ulp_v = findUPar(v);

    if(ulp_u == ulp_v)
        return;

    if(size[ulp_u] < size[ulp_v])
    {
        parent[ulp_u] = ulp_v;
        size[ulp_v] += size[ulp_u];
    }
    else
    {
        parent[ulp_v] = ulp_u;
        size[ulp_u] += size[ulp_v];
    }
}


